        <key>CKT.Clinical Guidance</key>
        <value>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Patient reports that he has never smoked. He has been exposed to tobacco smoke. He does not have any smokeless tobacco history on file.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Admission Tobacco use screen: Patient reports &amp;nbsp; to use of tobacco/tobacco like products in the past 30 days.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; to pharmacotherapy to reduce tobacco use during his admission.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;Assessing for Dependence&lt;br&gt;Interventions for nicotine withdrawal may be initiated during hospitalization to provide comfort to teens demonstrating nicotine dependence. Assess for dependence using the Hooked on Nicotine Checklist (HONC)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;https://ahsweb.ca/HEE/Hooked on NIcotine Checklist (HONC)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
